# Testing conventions

Always run tests with:

```bash
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=dummy pytest --cov=llm_fallbacks tests/ -v
```

## Layout

Flat `tests/` — no `conftest.py`, no shared fixtures file.

| File | Style |
|------|-------|
| `test_core.py` | Integration smoke against live LiteLLM registry; minimal mocking |
| `test_generate.py`, `test_quality.py` | Unit tests with inline fixture dicts; class-based grouping |

## Guidelines

- Match the style of the file you extend (integration vs inline-fixture unit)
- Use `from __future__ import annotations` and type annotations on locals when adding tests
- `test_core.py` assertions may shift with upstream model registry changes — avoid brittle model-id lists unless necessary
- Do not add drive-by lint fixes in test files
